// Issue #2651 accept side: a module referencing its OWN type both bare and
// through its own module qualifier. `selfqualtype.roundtrip()` passes a bare
// `Meter` (from `build()`) into a `selfqualtype.Meter` parameter (`read`),
// forcing the checker to compare bare `Meter` against `selfqualtype.Meter` with
// the current module set to `selfqualtype`. These are the SAME definition, so
// the owner-identity gate must accept the self-qualified alias — the strict
// comparison strips the redundant current-module self-qualifier. A regression
// here previously failed closed with a false
// `type mismatch: expected selfqualtype.Meter, found Meter`.
//
// Harness verb: hew run
// Expected: 3 — the bare `Meter` flows through the self-qualified parameter.
import hew::selfqualtype;

fn main() {
    println(f"{selfqualtype.roundtrip()}");
}
